The devastating floods in KZN has seen many good samaritans, including celebrities,  rallying together to lend a helping hand to families affected by the floods. Zakes Bantwini has roped in Nomcebo Zikode, Tbo Touch, DJ Tira, and Lekau Sehoana and called on others to hep them raise funds.  Nomcebo Zikode said the initiative has already helped raise an amount of R255 000 towards the cause.  Cassper Nyovest also shared how shattered he was about the ingoing floods that have hit Durban.  Shimza committed to doubling the amount of whatever they are able to put together for those who are in need.  Ntsiki Mazwai also urged social media users get big retailers to trend so they [the retailers] can donate water to the affected families.  For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.